@startuml
' @id(SEQ-VIEW-DEPLOY)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DEPLOY)
' @ref(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
' @desc(SEQ-VIEW-DEPLOY, "Objective flow for surfacing .mdd/deploy diagrams in `mdd view`. MddViewer::new() gains a third ingestion call, project.deploy_files(), beside model_registry() and cycle_registry(). deploy_files() reuses render_sources(RenderTree::Deploy) (the single source of truth for the deploy tree — OCL-RENDER-TREE-PARITY) and pairs each .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml with its rendered_pages_for() SVG mirror, returning plain ModelFile values WITHOUT inserting them into ModelRegistry. The viewer builds a separate TreeNode and renders it under a distinct, plainly-labelled DEPLOY section in BOTH rail modes; selecting a leaf reuses the existing load_file/DiagramPage path to paint .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Because the files never reach ModelRegistry, Project::review()/validate() (which read model_registry()) keep ignoring .mdd/deploy/.")
' Objective-side sequence: the dedicated, non-parity-gated DEPLOY source.
title mdd view — surface .mdd/deploy diagrams via a third source (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "mdd-cli\nCommands::View" as Cli
participant "MddViewer::new()" as Viewer
participant "Project\n(mdd-core)" as Core
participant "RenderTree::Deploy\nrender_sources()" as RT
database ".mdd/deploy/**/*.puml" as Deploy
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg" as Rendered

Dev -> Cli : mdd view
Cli -> Viewer : run(project)

group Two parity-gated sources (unchanged)
  Viewer -> Core : model_registry()  (.mdd/models + .mdd/constraints)
  Viewer -> Core : cycle_registry()  (.mdd/cycles)
end

group Third source — DEPLOY (new, NOT gated)
  Viewer -> Core : deploy_files()
  Core -> RT : render_sources(RenderTree::Deploy)
  RT -> Deploy : walk_suffix(".mdd/deploy", ".puml")
  Deploy --> RT : [diagram.puml ...]
  RT --> Core : sources
  Core -> Core : rendered_pages_for(rel)\n-> ModelFile{ rendered_pages }
  note right of Core
    Returned as plain ModelFile values.
    NOT pushed into ModelRegistry, so
    /mdd-validate and /mdd-review never
    see them — parity gate untouched.
  end note
  Core --> Viewer : Vec<ModelFile> (deploy)
end

Viewer -> Viewer : TreeNode::build(deploy)\nrender "DEPLOY · utility, not parity-gated"\n(shown in Directory AND By-cycle)
Dev -> Viewer : click deploy leaf
Viewer -> Viewer : load_file(file)  (existing path)
Viewer -> Rendered : read .mdd/rendered/deploy/<rel>.svg
Rendered --> Viewer : SVG bytes
Viewer --> Dev : deployment diagram painted on canvas

note over Deploy, Rendered
  If the .svg mirror is absent the canvas shows the
  same "not rendered — run mdd render" placeholder as
  any unrendered model. The viewer never rasterizes;
  `mdd render` already covers RenderTree::Deploy.
end note
@enduml
